wytr.item.accessory.Abominator.lore: Who would have thought to ever design something as pointlessly contrived and unusable as this? It's infuriating just to think about...
wytr.item.accessory.Abrasion.lore: "The fractures have ground the land to dust, our home to ruin, and our people to nothing."
wytr.item.accessory.AbyssalAmulet.lore: Used by the Order of the Abyss to aid their summoning rituals, it contains a strange, fiery energy. It has ties with a terrible demon...
wytr.item.accessory.AdderStone.lore: Aldorei charms are often shared and tinkered with by gifted Elves within the commune. Though simple, the stones blessed by elven magic provide soothing energy to the wearer.
wytr.item.accessory.AfelissLocket.lore: A golden locket Afelis always carried with them. Inside is a picture of Afelis embracing a woman in the Detlas square. 'A+E' is inscribed on the front.
wytr.item.accessory.Albatross.lore: And lo, a single bolt did fly, ensured the bird's grace ever lost, and pierced its wings out from the sky, the day you shot the albatross.
wytr.item.accessory.AltumSpatium.lore: Even looking at this pendant strains your eyes. Should it even exist?
wytr.item.accessory.Ambivalence.lore: "It's all doomed anyway. If you don't care, nothing can hurt you." - Zamugnia, Lost Lutho Citizen
wytr.item.accessory.AnyasPenumbra.lore: "The lightest light will never defeat the darkest dark. Only those who understand both can survive."
wytr.item.accessory.ApexPredator.lore: Something must always rule the ecosystem, even one as warped as this.
wytr.item.accessory.Atavistic.lore: In the wake of the Decay, the land yearns to return to its old vibrance.
wytr.item.accessory.Athanasia.lore: May your triumphs live eternal and never fade.
wytr.item.accessory.BindingBrace.lore: An oppressively dark aura emanates from this shackle, dampening both the will and magic potency of those that wear it.
wytr.item.accessory.BlackCatalyst.lore: Even simply looking at these odd rings gives way to a compulsion to wear two of them, despite all better judgement.
wytr.item.accessory.BlackSpace.lore: Give yourself to darkness, and in darkness, answers will take shape.
wytr.item.accessory.Breakthrough.lore: An anomaly of destruction, for the conquerors who seek purpose outside of reality.
wytr.item.accessory.BrokenSandust.lore: The silver looks rather tarnished...does he expect you to believe that "gem" isn't just a cheap glass bauble?
This bracelet is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.
This necklace is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.
wytr.item.accessory.BronzeBasicRing.lore: This ring is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.
wytr.item.accessory.BusterBracer.lore: A mighty, earth-shatteringly powerful weapon was destroyed for fear of its raw power, and the pieces buried. They were unearthed decades later, and were reforged into various items including this sturdy bracer.
wytr.item.accessory.Cacophony.lore: Let their souls sing your chorus of victory.
wytr.item.accessory.CalltoConcord.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] Reverberating with the bravery and residual strength of fallen Wynn soldiers, every casualty only serves to harden the resolve it instills in the wearer.
wytr.item.accessory.ChippedGlitz.lore: There are little chips and cracks all over this... was someone trying to break it down for gold?
wytr.item.accessory.ColdWave.lore: Feeling the fresh chill of the cold air is all you need to know you're really alive.
wytr.item.accessory.Collection.lore: An anomaly of adoption, for the caretakers who seek purpose outside of reality.
wytr.item.accessory.Compliance.lore: "All of our faith, all of our worship, and we were rewarded with the apocalypse."
wytr.item.accessory.Concentration.lore: The forger of this ring had to endure 30 long days of smelting various metals only found in the ocean. A single mistake would ruin the creation. The mystic metals are said to seep into the wearers skin to gently replenish their resolve.
wytr.item.accessory.Contrast.lore: The runes carved onto the gold beads strung along this simple necklace translate into various words meaning variance. It provides many abilities though unexplainable means.
wytr.item.accessory.CrackedStonehall.lor: It looks like someone tried and failed to improve it. The re-smithing job was obviously rushed...
wytr.item.accessory.Daredevil.lore: The mangled body found days too late apparently thought this necklace would let them traverse between geysers into the Upper Heights.
wytr.item.accessory.Detachment.lore: An anomaly of separation, for the wanderers who seek purpose outside of reality.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondFiberBracelet: Desired by many of the countless challengers, this bracelet allows you to sense movements over thousands of meters away. It is decorated with rough yet beautiful jewels.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondFiberNecklace: This ultimate version of a necklace was given to less than a handful of adventurers. Once on your neck, you can communicate with the ground below as if you grew roots.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondFiberRing.lor: This masterpiece of a ring utilizes powerful electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Wearing it, you can feel a deep connection to the ground below.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondFusionBracele: This bracelet opens up its wearers spirit, filling it with pure elemental knowledge. The ornaments decorating it are without peer.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondFusionNecklac: Unlike any other invention this necklace enhances your power and understanding of the elements tenfold. The colorful jewels used are almost dizzying you.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondFusionRing.lo: This mighty ring is the crown jewel amongst elemental rings. Wearing it, your knowledge is no longer limited to a few elements.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondHydroBracelet: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this bracelet on your arm you could ride a wave with your bare feet.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondHydroNecklace: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said and every word was true. With this necklace equipped, you could hear the ocean whisper.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondHydroRing.lor: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this ring on your finger, you could catch a gnat without looking.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondSolarBracelet: The device forged into this perfected bracelet drains all heat from its surroundings. Though it almost burns, you can feel your power growing
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondSolarNecklace: The masterpiece of a necklace gathers all heat from its surrounding. It is fed to its wearer to maximize the strength of attacks.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondSolarRing.lor: The device forged into this flawless ring draws all heat from its surrounding. Though it almost burns, you can feel your abilites enhance.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondStaticBracele: The heavy shocks coming from this perfected bracelet would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is the enhancement of power.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondStaticNecklac: The lethal amount of electricity emmited from this often desired necklace fails to kill you, as its pure energy runs through your veins.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondStaticRing.lo: The heavy electrical impulses coming from this ring would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is pure power. A true masterpiece of engineering.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondSteamBracelet: This steam-powered bracelet is sought by many challengers of the Legendary Challenge. They say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondSteamNecklace: This necklace is the pinnacle of steam-powered technology. Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from the necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all.
wytr.item.accessory.DiamondSteamRing.lor: Users of this perfect model of Legendary Island's steam-powered ring have reported feeling weightless in combat. The jewel of the ring is a perfectly clear diamond.
wytr.item.accessory.DilutedVitriol.lore: The glass capsule holding the poison vial is too cloudy to see what's inside. The merchant's reassurances are anything but.
wytr.item.accessory.Dispersion.lore: "The lucky ones perished in the abyss. It’s only a matter of time before the land picks us survivors off one by one."
wytr.item.accessory.Downfall.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] A fallen link from a chainmail hauberk of an older time, this ring fell from a giant taller than a mountain. As it sped through the air and  gained momentum, it traveled so fast that it was battered to a tenth of its size.
wytr.item.accessory.DulledAmethystRing.l: The merchant insists the gem is real. It's easy to tell that the issue is the quality of the gem, though...
wytr.item.accessory.DurumsSerenity.lore: Carried by the Durum Protector, this small necklace holds but an ounce of the vibrance and life of the Durum Isles.
wytr.item.accessory.EnsasFaith.lore: The scholar-priest Ensa created this pendant as a personal prayer while his home was under siege. It is rumored to hold the key to enlightenment, but it is unknown as to how.
wytr.item.accessory.Extinction.lore: The Decay swept away countless species. As those memories die, they are lost forever.
wytr.item.accessory.EyesonAll.lore: A presence of despair watches over the swamp as the Decay spreads.
wytr.item.accessory.Field.lore: "After the Nivla forest fire, I'm glad the corrupteds haven't thought to try and burn the Detlas Suburbs." -Sergeant Klafson, Detlas Legion
wytr.item.accessory.FollowtheWind.lore: A lost relic from the Wind Fortress, a mythical stronghold of the Sky Islands that fell into the Void long ago. A small mechanism within the bracelet points towards its place of origin.
wytr.item.accessory.Forbearance.lore: An anomaly of restriction, for the protectors who seek purpose outside of reality.
wytr.item.accessory.FoundFootage.lore: Despite heavy damage, this memory core recovered from a fallen Despermech remains usable. Sifting through its contents paints a clear yet brutal picture of the destruction the rogue creations have caused.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldFiberBracelet.lo: This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can feel a rhythm with each step...
wytr.item.accessory.GoldFiberNecklace.lo: This improved version of a bracelet utilizes rare electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You notice a rhythm with each step...
wytr.item.accessory.GoldFiberRing.lore: This improved ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can sense a rhythm with each step...
wytr.item.accessory.GoldFusionBracelet.l: This bracelet, decorated with complex ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. Though powerful, there's still a lot to improve.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldFusionNecklace.l: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses advanced nano-technology to boost its users elemental abilities. Though powerful, there are still a few flaws to be fixed.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldFusionRing.lore: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a powerful elemental force in you. Though stronger than the previous model, its true potential stays sealed.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldHydroBracelet.lo: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?
wytr.item.accessory.GoldHydroNecklace.lo: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?
wytr.item.accessory.GoldHydroRing.lore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant insisted. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?
wytr.item.accessory.GoldSolarBracelet.lo: The device forged into this improved bracelet seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your arm...
wytr.item.accessory.GoldSolarNecklace.lo: The device forged into this advanced necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your neck...
wytr.item.accessory.GoldSolarRing.lore: The device forged into this advanced ring seems to absorb heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your hand...
wytr.item.accessory.GoldStaticBracelet.l: The painful shock coming from this improved version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldStaticNecklace.l: The strong shock coming from this improved version of the necklace is a small price for its strength, but it has yet to reach its peak.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldStaticRing.lore: The strong shock coming from this advanced version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldSteamBracelet.lo: This impressive bracelet is in high demand. Those who have obtained it say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldSteamNecklace.lo: The jewel hanging from this necklace is said to be weightless. While still very powerful, its full potential has yet to be achieved.
wytr.item.accessory.GoldSteamRing.lore: While this model of the Steam Ring is far superior to its predecessor, there still lies the capacity for one more upgrade. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.
wytr.item.accessory.HexMasterAnchor.lore: Having felt the power of the Keep's hex, this jewel carries a familiar weight. Much like the Hex-Masters before you, you find channeling curses comes like second nature.
wytr.item.accessory.HexedAmulet.lore: Although the warlock's curse placed upon this simple, Olux-crafted charm will reduce the abilities of the wearer significantly, its original luck-bolstering properties still are in place.
wytr.item.accessory.Homeorhesis.lore: Stability is not necessarily found in stasis, but predictability.
wytr.item.accessory.Hypoxia.lore: You need to keep moving. You can't stop here. You can't. You can't breathe. You can't run. You're dying. You can't keep on. You can't. You can't.
wytr.item.accessory.Ingress.lore: An anomaly of invasion, for the explorers who seek purpose outside of reality.
wytr.item.accessory.Intensity.lore: The runes carved into this simple gold ring translate into various words meaning power. It amplifies elemental energies in inexplicable ways.
wytr.item.accessory.JiandanHandwraps.lor: The cloth wraps produced by the canyon Dojo are just that, merely soft cloth. It is left to the users to apply them skillfully in battle, in whatever way they see fit.
wytr.item.accessory.KaloriteJewel.lore: A symbol of apology. Of pain, never intended but given carelessly. Of good intentions marred by thoughtlessness and overeager optimism. To give one of these icy pearls away is to give away part of yourself,  and to give hope to those you have hurt that they may find peace.
wytr.item.accessory.Kaze.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] Gentle spirits of the wind attract themselves to the brilliant jewels slotted into this ring, bringing peace to its wearers and those around them.
wytr.item.accessory.Knucklebones.lore: An old Nemract saying is engraved along the metal. "A single toss of the knucklebones can make or break a gambling man."
wytr.item.accessory.LawoftheJungle.lore: An uncountably old relic of Time Valley which has changed owners only through death, there is an inscription carved on it: '⒠⒜⒯ ⒪⒭ ⒝⒠ ⒠⒜⒯⒠⒩'
wytr.item.accessory.LegendaryMedallion.l: This medallion marks its wearer as a true champion. It is awarded to those who have put an unnecessary amount of time into attempting the Legendary Challenge.
wytr.item.accessory.Lodestone.lore: The magical oddity known as lodestone has been studied for years as an active counterpart to quartz's passive magical properties. Research continues, but it is valuable when creating magical items.
wytr.item.accessory.LostSeconds.lore: This ring is set with a beautiful, mesmerizing gem. You could look at it for hours. Hours and hours and hours.
wytr.item.accessory.Martyr.lore: A recently married man went off to war wearing this wedding ring. Though he perished in battle, his courage and determination empowers all who wear it.
wytr.item.accessory.Marvel.lore: The stellar quality of the coral jewels set into the ring comes from a magical purification process, involving a decade-long soak in mystical Gylia water.
wytr.item.accessory.Master.lore: Although not truly magical by any means, the sheer craftsmanship of this ornate broach makes its wearers feel skillful.
wytr.item.accessory.Metamorphosis.lore: What you have seen will mark you forever.
wytr.item.accessory.MisshapenLibella.lor: It's completely impossible to use this for its intended purpose now. It barely can fit on your finger as is.
wytr.item.accessory.Momentum.lore: This golden cuff has an odd time dilation effect surrounding it, slowing all movements significantly, but multiplying the force of impact to a significant degree.
wytr.item.accessory.NecklaceofaThousandS: Sealed away by the Avos of the old days to prevent it from falling into the wrong hands, this necklace was enchanted to strengthen its wearers spiritual link to nature itself.
wytr.item.accessory.Obstinance.lore: "The protector will keep us safe even after this! It has to, it must, it—"
wytr.item.accessory.OldKeepersRing.lore: Found on the corpse of the oldest shopkeeper of the Gavel province, the engraved text reads 'GREED'.
wytr.item.accessory.PlanetHealer.lore: The jewels in this necklace naturally draw darkness and corruption into its wearer, purifying the land around them at the cost of their own life.
wytr.item.accessory.Precious.lore: A strange magic attracts you to this ring. Maybe you shouldn't tell anyone about its existence?
wytr.item.accessory.Prism.lore: The jewel on this ring is found very rarely deep beneath the Light Forest. It has the power to manipulate light itself.
wytr.item.accessory.Provenance.lore: Your success heralds the beginning of something new.
wytr.item.accessory.Prowess.lore: The runes carved into this simple gold cuff translate into various words meaning mastery. It amplifies the ability of the wearer in mysterious ways.
wytr.item.accessory.Ra.lore: Undecipherable symbols are carved into this long arm band, though the fiery glow and bright jewel has led archaeologists to believe it is somehow related to the sun.
wytr.item.accessory.Rarity.lore: Being one of the absolute rarest treasures in the world, it seems to have a mind of its own, only showing itself when a stroke of luck is had.
wytr.item.accessory.Recalcitrance.lore: "The omens, the warnings, they were right there, and we stood by and did nothing."
wytr.item.accessory.Reckoning.lore: Come to terms with your godlike judgment.
wytr.item.accessory.RemikasAuthority.lor: This plain-looking silver bracer is one of the last surviving heirlooms of the first Gavellian king, to be passed down to his heirs. The shimmering metal is said to contain Remikas' soul within it.
wytr.item.accessory.RoyalBlazingAmulet.l: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It glows with a comforting warmth.
wytr.item.accessory.RoyalCycloneAmulet.l: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It whistles with an invigorating tune.
wytr.item.accessory.RoyalDustyAmulet.lor: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It shines with a powerful strength.
An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It crackles with a chaotic energy.
wytr.item.accessory.RoyalStormyAmulet.lo: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It pulsates with a calming aura.
wytr.item.accessory.RycarsElation.lore: Created from the lip of a wine bottle and dropped in the mystic waters of Lake Gylia, this glass ring seems to follow Rycar's drunken escapades wherever she wanders.
wytr.item.accessory.Shatterglass.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] This small, rough-crafted pendant is the only known magic artifact of the Orcs. It incites destructive tendencies within the wearer.
This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.
This crude looking necklace utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains quiet.
wytr.item.accessory.SilverFiberRing.lore: This crude looking ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.
wytr.item.accessory.SilverFusionBracelet: This bracelet, decorated with simple ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.
wytr.item.accessory.SilverFusionNecklace: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.
wytr.item.accessory.SilverFusionRing.lor: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a strong elemental affinity in you. With some improvements to its core, it could become even better...
You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.
You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.
wytr.item.accessory.SilverHydroRing.lore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.
The device forged into this simple bracelet seems to gather heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...
The device forged into this basic necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warm sting when holding it.
wytr.item.accessory.SilverSolarRing.lore: The device forged into this simple ring seems to absorb heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...
wytr.item.accessory.SilverStaticBracelet: Though it's hard to touch the simple, mechanical bracelet without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...
wytr.item.accessory.SilverStaticNecklace: Though it's hard to touch the plain, tech-enhanced necklace without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...
wytr.item.accessory.SilverStaticRing.lor: Though it's hard to touch the plain, mechanical ring without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...
Users who have worn this early model of the Steam Bracelet have reported that they have felt "one with the wind" while wearing it.
Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from this necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all. However, the necklace's mechanisms seem incomplete.
wytr.item.accessory.SilverSteamRing.lore: This prototype model of the Steam Ring increases the user's agility in combat. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.
wytr.item.accessory.Simulacrum.lore: An anomaly of replication, for the assemblers who seek purpose outside of reality.
wytr.item.accessory.SpanoftheStarfield.l: Infinitesimal specks of matter wane in and out of view among the darkness of this clasp. Even a glance reminds you of what little exists in the expanses of the Void from which the materials of this were scavenged from.
wytr.item.accessory.SpiderRing.lore: "Crawly things. They crawl on the mushrooms. Mushrooms shouldn't be crawly!" -Yahya, Mushroom Man
wytr.item.accessory.Stellar.lore: Elementally attuned gemstones are melded together to form the singular marvel found on this pendant. Despite the violent smithing process, the jewel is utterly flawless.
wytr.item.accessory.StickyDecoderRing.lo: Each one is welded stuck to just one letter. Apparently, to decode the special Rymek message, you need to buy twenty six. ...do they think you're a fool?
wytr.item.accessory.Succession.lore: "I pray that those who have heeded the wise one’s warning have survived. The canyon must not meet this fate."
wytr.item.accessory.Summa.lore: An auxiliary power core of the powerful TERA-4M Mining robot line. It controls the robots by giving the bearer a compulsion to break new grounds and progress further without heed.
wytr.item.accessory.SweetMemories.lore: The feel of cool cream. The savory satisfaction of fatty stew. The bittersweetness of chocolate. Luxuries long since lost alongside what once was, tastes and sensations you can't find anymore. It's enough to bring a man to bitter, bitter tears.
wytr.item.accessory.Symbiont.lore: Survival is the shared interest of those in the wilds.
wytr.item.accessory.Tenuto.lore: This strange pendant has been known to dilate time around the wearer, slowing their movements while greatly augmenting their power.
wytr.item.accessory.TheExtinguished.lore: Everything that’s fallen down here has a purpose. Or at least, it used to. Being too far removed from said purpose will eventually smother it, but it can always be rekindled... and that’s where you come in.
wytr.item.accessory.Umami.lore: Rumors circulate of a once-cook from Lutho who managed to achieve the perfect meal. In their final days, they preserved its essence in this necklace, in a hope that someone else would be able to share the experience they had.
wytr.item.accessory.Unspeakable.lore: The wielders of this cursed glassen bauble are rendered mute. The effect is reversed after the item is removed, but the longer it is worn, the longer the curse remains.
wytr.item.accessory.UsedWolfPaw.lore: It looks more like a dog paw to you, but you don't feel like risking your life arguing with the merchant.
wytr.item.accessory.Veneration.lore: Revel in the respect you've finally earned.
wytr.item.accessory.Vitre.lore: "They say the eyes are the windows to the soul. That's ridiculous, ocular fluids are primarily opaque." -Ragon, Elemental Researcher
wytr.item.accessory.WeightedNimbleFinger: The extra metal on the glove completely defeats the purpose... It's unclear why it was re-smithed like this.
"My dear boy should never have to go through the horrors of losing a mother like that." -Momo, adoptive mother of Bob
wytr.item.accessory.WynnterFair2016Souve: Thank you for participating in the 2016 Wynnter Fair!
wytr.item.accessory.WynnterFair2017Souve: Thank you for participating in the 2017 Wynnter Fair!
wytr.item.accessory.Wynnterfest2016Souve: Thank you for participating in Wynnterfest 2016!
wytr.item.armour.Abdomen.lore: "...But under no circumstances should you stand directly behind an attacking spider. While not a universal trait, some spiders are capable of ejecting webs from their spinneret, leaving assailants and victims helpless." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3
wytr.item.armour.Abiogenesis.lore: Life itself is not a flexible material to work with—building sentience is precisely like squeezing blood from a stone. It may be years of toil, but the strength of an entire race that looks to you as a creator cannot be overstated.
wytr.item.armour.AbyssImbuedLeggings.lor: Steeped in the deepest energies of the Ahms region void, these ornately-crafted leggings are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.AbyssoGaloshes.lore: Rumored to be crafted from a Dernic stone, these sinister boots radiate extremely powerful dark energy. They have absorbed the power of the raging seas in their time locked in Sarnfic.
wytr.item.armour.Adamantite.lore: Adamantite is a soft metal often added to exotic medicine to increase one's health, but a revolutionary blacksmith on Black Road, created a chestplate with an Adamantite alloy, which is advertised to bolster the users endurance.
wytr.item.armour.Adherence.lore: Adherence to the laws of good is important- it’s why one fights the spread of corruption, after all. Though whether to follow the spirit or the letter… perhaps they too can be bent to your will.
wytr.item.armour.AlephNull.lore: It's a strange feeling, running forever to reach the horizon knowing another lies just as far past.
wytr.item.armour.AlmujsWalker.lore: There used to be a constant battle between Almuj's thieves over these feather-light, gold-plated boots, until one day they were stolen by an unknown pickpocket and never seen again.
wytr.item.armour.Alternator.lore: Llevigar's schools of wizardry are notorious for their difficult training regimens. These leg plates, forcing users to balance spellcasting with direct combat, are often cited as the tipping point for successful wizards.
wytr.item.armour.Anchoryl.lore: Despite being a much smaller settlement compared to the mighty citadel of Rodoroc, the dwarven smiths of Thanos still can forge mighty products, such as these heavy diamond-alloy boots.
wytr.item.armour.AndesiteAegis.lore: Andesite is a stone commonly used for weapons and construction, but tends to be ineffective as armor when impure. This sturdy chestplate, however, is testament to the strength of pure andesite.
wytr.item.armour.AnimaInfusedCuirass.lor: Infused with the classical magicks of fire, water, and thunder, this ornately-crafted chestplate is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.Antebellum.lore: Only the naive celebrate a ceasefire. Not a second wasted, a merciless arms race against the inevitability of war has left you ready to unleash hell the moment the armistice breaks.
wytr.item.armour.Aphorism.lore: Just because it's been said to death doesn't mean it isn't true.
wytr.item.armour.Aphotic.lore: This dark relic was found at the very bottom of the deepest trench of the ocean. It drains all light surrounding it, blinding everything in a strange abyssal darkness.
wytr.item.armour.Aquarius.lore: “The symbol of the river” is a name that is often synonymous with this garment, with many water like qualities surrounding it, heavily bathed in magical meaning.
wytr.item.armour.ArakadicusBody.lore: Long strips of chitin discarded from the mother of spiders Arakadicus still contain traces of her wicked powers, but few have survived the attempts to harvest them.
wytr.item.armour.Aries.lore: Two iron horns adorn this helmet to enhance the warriors of the Eradian, Dwarves who specifically rode Rams into battle at incredible speed.
wytr.item.armour.Asphyxia.lore: A condition of severely deficient supply of oxygen to the body that arises from abnormal breathing; practitioners that abuse specific magic combos are often found incapacitated by said condition.
wytr.item.armour.Audacity.lore: A powerful mental curse surrounds these boots, inciting uncontrollable rage into the wearers, as well as the power to enact it upon others.
wytr.item.armour.BadWolf.lore: The runic message carved on these enigmatic boots cover hundreds of different languages, many of them disused, but what has been translated seems to describe a disaster soon to arrive to the world.
wytr.item.armour.BeigeWynnterSweater.lor: The sweater has the quote "All STOCKINGED up for the season" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.BlackRipper.lore: "The skeletons at Ancient Nemract are rotted! is it even physically possible to rot a bone?" -Laen, Nemract Librarian
wytr.item.armour.BlackWynnterSweater.lor: The sweater has the quote "Prepare for a FLURRY of Craftmas spirit" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.BlessedWrappings.lore: The thick, Bovemist-sanctified cloth is worn by their priests during certain religious ceremonies. It clears the mind and purifies the body.
wytr.item.armour.BloodMoon.lore: Imbued with the blood of the first werewolf, it was kept in Gelibord as a trophy before being stolen. Wearing it is said to mimic the effects of the lycanthropic curse.
wytr.item.armour.BlueMask.lore: The Blue Mask's physical traits are equal to that of paper, but the mystical properties enhance the wearers personal skills tenfold. The mask is thought to originate from an ancient Dernel tribe.
wytr.item.armour.BlueWynnterSweater.lore: The sweater has the quote "Don't feel BLUE- It's Craftmas!" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.BobsBattleChestplate.lo: This battered chestplate was once worn by the legendary Wynnic protector, Bob, during the fearsome corrupted sieges before he gave it away to an old friend. An air of melancholy hangs over it.
wytr.item.armour.BoosterPlate.lore: A marvel of Corkus' electromagical advancements, this high-tech chestplate is equipped with steam jets to boost the user's speed, at a minimal cost to protection.
wytr.item.armour.Boreal.lore: The last known crafts of Theorick before his fall in battle were pieces of armour crafted out of pure ice, all of which have melted save for these shimmering boots. The coldest gales and most suffocating heat nurture and repair the wearer instead of being stifling or deadly.
wytr.item.armour.BorealPatternedCrown.lo: Engraved with the beauty and mystery of the boreal lights, this ornately-crafted crown is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.BovineKiller.lore: This helmet was worn long ago by an infamous assassin who plagued Bovemist sites for decades. It was crafted of the still-bloody skin of their most prized and worshiped cows.
wytr.item.armour.BridgeoftheDivide.lore: These leggings hold the interest of many researching the corruption, as they are the only documented case of a non-corrupt fusion of dark and light energy, made of pure twilight.
wytr.item.armour.Brise.lore: "With the hot, dry winds from the Roots and the cold, wet winds from Nesaak, these houses rot faster than you can blink." -Viraex, Elkurn Citizen
wytr.item.armour.BrokenBalance.lore: Torn scraps of metal line the inside of these boots. They provide no protection, instead forcing a constant adrenaline rush while worn.
wytr.item.armour.BrownWynnterSweater.lor: The sweater has the quote "YULE see me smiling this season" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.Butterfly.lore: "Time travel cares less about small things like a flapping wing, and more about big things, like becoming your own grandfather." -Martyn, Time Valley Resident
wytr.item.armour.CageofBones.lore: The ancient bones of the demon Garaheth are stronger than steel. They clamp down when worn to constrict the bearer, inciting a slow madness.
wytr.item.armour.CalloftheVoid.lore: Originating from the unspeakable dark land, looking into the helmet will show nothing but darkness. Wearing it is said to reverse your morality, as if it were draining your will to live into the void.
wytr.item.armour.Cannonade.lore: An impenetrable fortress’ greatest strength is psychological, a mythos built on the backs of a thousand attackers it has withstood. Your greatest strength is the belief that not one of those thousand could hold a candle to you.
wytr.item.armour.Capricorn.lore: During a spiritual journey to Kato temple, the sage Capian was presented with powerful spiritual boots with the intention to be used for peaceful magic, and not hard combat.
wytr.item.armour.CardiacArrest.lore: ...As the heart fails, adrenaline pumps through the body in an attempt to provide energy and keep the victim alive, but medical action must be taken to ensure survival. -Excerpt from Aldorei Medical Tomes, Vol. 6
wytr.item.armour.Cephalothorax.lore: "...Most of their vital organs, however, are located in the bulbous abdomen. If you've enough crushing force with your weapon, it may be a quicker alternative for the kill. ..." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3
wytr.item.armour.CeridsIngenuity.lore: One of the master tinkerer Cerid's greatest inventions, these odd gear-laced boots clink and chime with the sound of clockworks keeping its powerful magic dynamos constantly running.
The sweater has the quote "SLOPE to SKI you again next Craftmas" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.ChainedPixels.lore: Materials of all sorts have been lashed together in this crude, blocky set of leggings. From darksteel to leather to rotting wood, each part is a perfect square. It has, so far, been impossible to recreate.
wytr.item.armour.ChaosWovenGreaves.lore: With threads of fundamentally opposing magic delicately woven together, these ornately-crafted greaves are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.Chimaera.lore: The one true Chimera in existence is sought by many, for great stories are told of its gifts to the worthy. One such gift was a simple fur coat, which gave the wearer but a taste of its power.
wytr.item.armour.CinfrasSouvenirTShirt.l: The shirt has the quote "I went to the Letvus Airbase in Cinfras and all I got was this lousy T-shirt" printed on it.
wytr.item.armour.ClearsightSpectacles.lo: Ancient magicks are required to make these brilliant glasses, imbued with charity and selflessness. They allow sight beyond sight, rumoured to allow sight of a brilliant realm.
wytr.item.armour.CoeurBrise.lore: Left to brittle introspection, love unrequited stings the most when it brings down something built to last.
wytr.item.armour.Conductor.lore: Using an unorthodox method of smithing, these copper leggings are insulated with an extremely conductive blend of liquid to improve electrical discharge.
wytr.item.armour.Conflagrate.lore: Donning this helmet sears your mind with images of a world on fire. These blistering thoughts pressure you to make that world a reality.
wytr.item.armour.ConspiratorsTrickpocket: No reign lasts forever. Not while your schemes remain unnoticed.
wytr.item.armour.CrusadeSabatons.lore: One of the very few physically-powerful artifacts of the Villagers, these boots were used in the initial crusades against the Green-skins, to overpower the Orcs via raw physical might. Though effective, they have not seen use in a long time.
wytr.item.armour.Crystal.lore: Forged on Mage Island, the sparkling liquid-like armour is as hard as obsidian, but light and fluid as water. It glistens with the magic of the ocean winds.
wytr.item.armour.Cyclo.lore: A centuries-old storm spirit was banished to these tight boots for his destructive actions. His fury empowers those who wear them with the great force of a raging cyclone.
wytr.item.armour.DarkShroud.lore: Wearing this deceptively simple shroud causes the user to fade into the shadows, sometimes flickering out of existence for a moment.
wytr.item.armour.DarkironScrap.lore: Despite being only an impure scrap of the normally sturdy blackiron, these heavy leggings still have extreme defensive capabilities.
wytr.item.armour.Dawnbreak.lore: Many prophecies foretell of new eras. Most are fabricated or proven false in time. One passed through the Dogun caverns, however, tells of a dawn soon to break, in which the earth shall run red and return to flame. Fanatical sects whisper the coming of a new demonic god.
wytr.item.armour.DeadSamuraisPlate.lore: "We get a lot of weirdos coming from Gavel by airship. That plate mail looked unusably ornate!" -Calo, Private Airship Operator
wytr.item.armour.DeadSands.lore: Found in the middle of the Almuj desert, these greaves seem to slowly poison all life around them. Theorists suggest they were the handiwork of a wicked necromancer, though the truth is not known.
wytr.item.armour.Disco.lore: Recovered from a corrupted soldier who wore them, it was found dancing instead of attacking those around it. Even after it was killed, it jostled and jerked around like a dancing puppet.
wytr.item.armour.Discoverer.lore: Wealth and riches...but at what cost?
wytr.item.armour.DisfiguredVessel.lore: An imperfect fit, but you can make a better one.
wytr.item.armour.Dondasch.lore: The sheer bond between Adamastor and Urdar has manifested itself into a physical form due to their duress. Such power is not to be abused...
wytr.item.armour.DoomsdayOmen.lore: Something is lurking—it must be, in the eerie silence that leaves you so utterly alone. And these remains… Are they a reminder of one who didn’t stay quiet, or does what lurks in the unknown already know you’re here?
wytr.item.armour.DuneBeastJaw.lore: "We're trying to dig up history, not horrors! What is wrong with this province?!"  -Excavator Vade, WynnExcavation Site A Director
wytr.item.armour.EdenBlessedGuards.lore: Consecrated by Qira herself with blessings unknown to all but her, these ornately-crafted leggings are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.ElysiumEngravedAegis.lo: Dedicated to a place of courage revered by all warriors, this ornately-crafted chestplate is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedAssassinsHood.l: The chains comprising the mesh are rusty and old. It looks terrible, especially with the newer metal added on.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedCoalwalkers.lor: Even ignoring the numerous scorches all over, these boots hardly look any better.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedCopperPlate.lor: The merchant insists that the wear and oxidation on the armor "is a feature."
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedDuskshield.lore: They look extremely bulky and uncomfortable...do they have a right to call it "enhanced"?
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedGypsum.lore: The merchant launched into a tirade on how the hardness scale of stones means nothing the instant you saw part of the boots flake off upon being touched.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedHilltop.lore: Looks like it was hastily repainted to match the colors of the mesa. ...but you can see the original greens and browns underneath.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedIcarus.lore: Apparently, gluing some feathers on top of the decorative armor wings is supposed to allow you to fly- so says the merchant, at least.
The psalm tag has been replaced with a custom message from the armorer. What it says about the original owner is better left to the imagination.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedOxford.lore: They look like at once point they may have been fairly upscale. Now they just look like a metallic mess.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedPanorama.lore: They added stilts to the leggings, so that they could "live up to the name." The fact you can barely stand in them is neatly avoided when you ask.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedPhosphene.lore: The paintjob on the armor is incredibly garish. Who thinks to combine sea green, mud, hot pink, and neon yellow?
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedPickpockets.lor: Aside from the added plating, they look more or less intact. Somehow, that doesn't surprise you.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedSalience.lore: Adding hard metal onto a religious cap seems blasphemous to you. The merchant disagrees.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedSkeletonBoots.l: Some of the bones used to make the frame of the boots have crumbled. The merchant refuses to comment.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedUmbrellaHat.lor: The only difference you can see is that a tacky logo for Rymek Armoury has been stenciled onto the top.
wytr.item.armour.EnhancedZeal.lore: Supposedly this chestplate belonged to a legendary paladin. The merchant has no explanation for why there are dozens of them.
wytr.item.armour.Ephemeris.lore: A pair of glowing sabatons crafted from time-lost relics. Somehow, despite just creating them, you get the feeling that you've worn these before...
wytr.item.armour.EquinoxBlossom.lore: Perennial, in a sense—these plants cycle through a unique bloom for every season. When they fully form, the breathtaking equinox is said to shine with an otherworldly light.
wytr.item.armour.EradianCuissards.lore: Abandoned by the dwarven Ramriders in their heyday, this hefty armor forged to protect a steed sees little use but littering the steppes of the upper heights. A memento of a slaughter, in days long past.
wytr.item.armour.Erratio.lore: The blind prophet who crafted this macabre breastplate used the bones of only the most ruthless justiciars and executioners. Its wearers are supposedly destined to only die either a heroic or a just death.
wytr.item.armour.EsteemedBronzeMaskofLeg: Esteemed Bronze Mask of Legendary Victory
This decorative mask, crafted of bronze alloys, is awarded only to those who have spent an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge.
wytr.item.armour.Etiolation.lore: Despite the absence of natural light, in the deepest reaches of the Void grows foliage and flora capable of sustaining itself by absorbing latent energy. Such an accomplishment is to be admired, ideally from a keen distance.
wytr.item.armour.Fenmask.lore: This matted tangle of vines and marshland plants contains various herbal remedies woven into it. It is oddly comfortable, despite the thorns coating the inside.
wytr.item.armour.FragileTruce.lore: The enemy of your enemy is your friend. It’s naught but a ceasefire of convenience, if not necessity, yet it’s a chance to lick your wounds and focus your might against the threat at hand.
wytr.item.armour.Gadgeteer.lore: This suit was clearly designed by the hand of a mechanic, though its purpose is unknown. There are quite a lot of buttons on it though, so let’s press this one!
wytr.item.armour.GaeaHewnBoots.lore: Forged in direct tribute to the earth and its aspects, these ornately-crafted boots are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.GalesSight.lore: True to their promise, these goggles were left as a memento for Ohms when his lover Gale finally died. Light as air, Gale's carefree nature lends itself to those who don them.
wytr.item.armour.Galleon.lore: Forged with the raw powers of both the earth and the sea, these boots were initially an attempt at creating a method of foot-travel over the seas. Despite the spectacular failure of that application, they remain a formidable and reliable set of armor.
wytr.item.armour.GarothsHope.lore: "Strangest thing, it turns out Creepers are incredibly flammable..." -Garull, Cryptid Researcher
wytr.item.armour.Gemini.lore: The gods of air and thunder, frustrated with being physically insubstantial alone, decided to band together to forge the ultimate leggings of defense.
wytr.item.armour.GhostlyQuasar.lore: An eerie glimpse into what once was, shining beautifully in the infinite expanse of the Void. As tragic a tale it is, perhaps it is better left a wisp.
wytr.item.armour.GiantStep.lore: Found in a mystically-charged Giant ruin, these snug boots recall fond memories, incite calmness, and provide comfort for the wearer.
wytr.item.armour.GiantsBracer.lore: This ill-fitting, bulky chestplate was never intended to be a chestplate at all. Rather, it is a broken fragment of an arm bracer, from the time of giants.
wytr.item.armour.GoldDigger.lore: "With the corruption seemingly tied to the emeralds dug by the Roots, people thought gold was the next best thing, the idiots." -Gerald, Retired Miner
wytr.item.armour.Gravity.lore: No one knows how this extremely dense chestplate can even logically exist. It is almost paradoxical in nature, and affects its wearers in unfathomable ways.
wytr.item.armour.GreatbirdEyrie.lore: Sculpted by searing flames and dazzling light, in the years since the Fracturing the Greatbirds' nest has developed a blinding glow. It has both immense power and volatility, yet seems to hold a hidden strength for one who can tame its spirit.
wytr.item.armour.GreavesoftheVeneer.lore: Forged from mystic, previously unknown metals revealed in the deepest dwarven mining site to date, these sleek, glowing greaves are believed to be utterly indestructible.
wytr.item.armour.GreenWynnterSweater.lor: The sweater has the quote "I'm feeling PINE, what about you" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.Grillface.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] The old facemasks of the Eradian guards were forged from raw magma, and enchanted to remain searingly hot, so as to brand the wearer eternally with the mark of Rodoroc's elite.
wytr.item.armour.Heliophilia.lore: This peculiar shawl is eternally warm to the touch, and shimmers brilliantly in the sunlight. It is rumored to give amazing health benefits and good fortune to those who wear it.
wytr.item.armour.HephaestusForgedSabaton: Honoring a mythical dwarven smith lost to the legends, these ornately-crafted boots are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.HerosMask.lore: It bears the visage of a great hero. Thank you for participating in the Festival of the Heroes!
wytr.item.armour.Hetusol.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] The make of this massive cloak is unlike anything seen before among the provinces. Foreign images shift and melt in ethereal projections within the inside.
wytr.item.armour.HolyGreaves.lore: Many blacksmiths have tried to craft their products in this armor's image, but none so far have been able to capture the brilliance of these Bovemist-blessed greaves.
wytr.item.armour.Hunger.lore: Forgotten long ago, these boots curse the wearer with an endless hunger.
wytr.item.armour.ImpactWinter.lore: Do you think you can survive with a sky choked by snow and ash? More importantly, do you think anything else can?
wytr.item.armour.InconceivablyDerangedPa: Inconceivably Deranged Paper Mask of Legendary Victory

This cheap paper mask drawn in the likeness of Herbert von Legendary as he was having a complete nervous breakdown after having his life threatened by people who would not stop challenging him, is handed over in the ill-conceived hope of easing the murderous tendencies of those who have spent unnecessary amounts of time, broken the mold, gone even further beyond, pushed onward to prove that they will not stop, ultimately garnered an unhealthy obsession, and then came to blows in Doctor Legendary's house demanding further prizes all for the singularly unsettling and quite possibly sociopathic purpose of spending unnecessary amounts of time completing the Legendary Challenge. The inside has the names and addresses of multiple notable psychoanalysts written with a hastily-scrawled note from Doctor Legendary himself begging that you stop completing the Legendary Challenge and go get therapy before you do something to him that would constitute legal action against you.
wytr.item.armour.IndigoWynnterSweater.lo: The sweater has the quote "GRAUPELING with a second helping of Craftmas feast" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.InfernalImpulse.lore: If the depths of hell allows you this, is staying human an equal trade or a fool's choice?
wytr.item.armour.Insignia.lore: To wear the mark is more than a show of allegiance. It is a willingness to channel the might of the gods at whatever cost, as the fate of the battle is worth more than surviving to see its end.
wytr.item.armour.Iosis.lore: The last step towards purity. Dissolve and coagulate. Be anew.
wytr.item.armour.JungleRogue.lore: King of the Jungle—it's a title reserved for the apex of the apex, and yet from where you swing across the canopy, this beast of supposed royalty is but another victim of your thievish pursuits.
wytr.item.armour.KatoasWarmth.lore: Brilliantly golden as the crops from the humble farm, its mere presence fills stomachs and brings comfort, but only to those who are modest and generous.
wytr.item.armour.KelightsShield.lore: Used by the Temple of the Legends' strongest guard, the shielded plating is enchanted with a powerful ward to stave off the effects of the corruption.
wytr.item.armour.Keratoconus.lore: The unearthly wood of eyestalk is durable, but with horrific cost. Pieces severed from the trunk continue to collect and cultivate the essence of abandoned eyes, and the unfortunate wearer becomes a catalyst for growth.
wytr.item.armour.Knee.lore: "I thought aiming for the legs would disable the enemy. Turns out they can drag themselves with their arms just as quick." -Therck, Ragni Soldier 3rd Division
wytr.item.armour.Kratke.lore: Spurred on by a drunken bet, the great Thanos smith Kratke improved a pair of leggings from a rival that were once thought to be perfection.
wytr.item.armour.LemonLegs.lore: Due to an unfortunate accident where he choked on a lemon, an unremarkable mercenary became a laughing stock. He later managed to shed the title, as he left no one alive who remembered the name.
wytr.item.armour.Leo.lore: This thick skinned jacket, imbued with the courage of a thousand lion hearts, will grant the user massive protection from all who target them.
wytr.item.armour.Libra.lore: Before the invention of magical weight detectors, there was a giant pair of public scales in Cinfras. Instead of being thrown away, they were reforged to be a formidable piece of armour.
wytr.item.armour.LingeringTwilight.lore: In the harshest reaches of the mountains, dusk brings a gentle magic to the air, prolonging the faintest vestiges of sundown before night truly falls.
wytr.item.armour.LittleInferno.lore: It is cold to the touch until worn. Once donned, it engulfs the wearer in excruciatingly hot flames, but never shall the wearer burn; only their enemies will feel the pain of the fire.
wytr.item.armour.MariusPrison.lore: "I know the Beast may return one day...but these chains shall bind it for eternity." The inscription glows bright in the darkness.
wytr.item.armour.Martingale.lore: Every power has its costs, and every triumph has its toll. Wager everything you treasure—it will all be worth in the end.
wytr.item.armour.MaskoftheSpirits.lore: Not all who roam may find their way home. Others lose themselves in the world... And find a new way forward.
wytr.item.armour.MatryoshkaShell.lore: The armor worn by the enigmatic Matryoshka Idol. It appears to have a nearly uncountably high number of inlets and sockets set inside.
wytr.item.armour.Mazeweaver.lore: The strong can hammer foe and nature alike into submission, waging war with indiscriminate force. The truly powerful pit them against each other on a whim, weaving stone and verdure into an elaborate web of attrition that beats with the heart of an entire world. What is an enemy compared to all the might of the Earth?
wytr.item.armour.Meanderthal.lore: These boots were retrieved from a frozen man, uncovered on an expedition to Mt. Wynn. It is believed that the man had been wandering the world before his death.
wytr.item.armour.Memento.lore: All those who wear these enchanted boots deposit a single fond memory into them. They are forgotten forever, but wearing them recalls every memory within vividly.
wytr.item.armour.Millennium.lore: Cosmic energy permeates this deceptively dull-looking chestplate, having been crafted with stardust from a comet that only passes over Wynn every 1000 years.
wytr.item.armour.Moontower.lore: For the belief of the cosmos’ defilement, the moon was noted to remain unchanged. Those with this belief live only for the light of the moon, desperately seeking to maintain it through means that would only darken the soul of the most devout. Such from them comes the word lunacy.
wytr.item.armour.Mud.lore: "Some pigmen snuffle through dirt for things to eat. We dig up that soil to plant our crops in; it's always full of life." -Thomas, Ravine Village Resident
wytr.item.armour.MummysRag.lore: The accursed mummy once wore this robe as a great pharaoh of the desert. It has long since rotted, leaving only a cursed shell of its former greatness.
wytr.item.armour.MutilatedCorpse.lore: Freshly slain foes in well below freezing conditions often provide enough warmth to weather the storm. However, this Corrupted seems to still be alive in some sickening way, draining life force to sustain itself. It's pulling towards something.
wytr.item.armour.Necrosis.lore: 450 years ago a demonic plague like no other spread through Gavel, killing thousands. That is, until a priest encased the disease inside a helmet and warned everyone never to wear it.
wytr.item.armour.NemractsRuin.lore: This chestplate was originally created as a memorial ornament to the lost lives of Ancient Nemract before being reforged into a powerful piece of armor for Nemract's guard.
wytr.item.armour.Neolithic.lore: This ancient stone-hewn helmet is blended with the bones of an extinct animal of some kind. It is harder than dragon's hide.
wytr.item.armour.NethersScar.lore: Forged directly from the bloody red stone mined from the Nether, they were locked away for fear of inciting insanity in those who wore them.
wytr.item.armour.Nonexistence.lore: What lies beneath the brim of all that never was, that overflowing vastness which cannot spill?
wytr.item.armour.Nostalgia.lore: It once held little meaning, another lilac left unnoticed in the quotidian meadows of yesteryear. Yet just its scent brings forth a deluge of memory, crashing down with the force of a time long past.
wytr.item.armour.ObsidianFramedHelmet.lo: Made of dark minerals and adorned with pure obsidian, this ornately-crafted helmet is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.OhmsRage.lore: These ancient, spark-coursing greaves are all that remains of the great thunder mage Ohms' favorite golem familiar after a dark force turned it against its masters.
wytr.item.armour.OmnitreadBoots.lore: Plated with enchanted metals, these magic-warding boots allow faster travel over nearly any solid surface.
wytr.item.armour.Opulenity.lore: Made of an uncommonly used fabric called denim, these fashionable leggings exude style and elegance. Surely wearing them would bring you luck?
wytr.item.armour.OrangeWynnterSweater.lo: The sweater has the quote "ORANGE you glad I showed up for Craftmas" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.OutlandishReplicaFaceMa: Outlandish Replica Face Mask of Legendary Victory

This perfect-to-the-point-of-indistinguishability replica mask of Herbert von Legendary's face, painstakingly crafted by Corkus's most powerful machines with only the most expensive materials and featuring real moustache hair plucked from Doctor Legendary's face, is desperately handed over to attempt to placate those who have spent an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge, broken the mold by continuing to spend an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge, gone even further beyond spending unnecessary amounts of time completing the Legendary Challenge, pushed onward to prove that they will not stop spending unnecessary amounts of time completing the Legendary Challenge, and then ultimately garnered an unhealthy obsession for spending unnecessary amounts of time completing the Legendary Challenge.
wytr.item.armour.Outrage.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] This battered stone mask is of unknown origin, and has no openings for the eyes whatsoever. Indeed, all that can be seen while wearing it is that which makes you truly angry.
wytr.item.armour.PainCycle.lore: Every ounce of your suffering must be made worth it. Otherwise, what was the point of it all?
wytr.item.armour.PassusLux.lore: A brilliant relic supposedly originating from the Realm of Light, the creators of these strangely shaped boots are completely unknown.
wytr.item.armour.Pelier.lore: Occasional whisperings can be heard by the wearers of this stone mask, reforged from a phylactery of souls. Although not dangerous, staring into the eyes of the mask can bring fear of one's soul being trapped within.
wytr.item.armour.PerchoftheShroudedSun.l: Able to withstand the grasp of claws of pure steel, the perch of the Minokawa thrums with the might of a beast that can devour the sun. Given free reign of the skies, even the brightest of stars are no match.
wytr.item.armour.PhagePins.lore: Salvaged from the limbs of the Vulcor Adrenophage, they radiate extreme heat,  suffusing the body they attach to with that same heat. It almost feels as though your blood is heating to a frenetic boil.
wytr.item.armour.PhantasmalHostage.lore: A soul sacrificed willingly, to an eternity in captivity. Imprints and memories; all that remain of a hero of the lands.
wytr.item.armour.PhantasmalRemnants.lore: Memories take on lives of their own, left long enough.
wytr.item.armour.Philosopher.lore: What better excuse is there to sit in the shade and think about life?
wytr.item.armour.PhoenixPrincesCrown.lor: The Phoenix Prince is a mythical figure spoken of in Avos legend. His crown cursed him in an endless cycle of death and rebirth.
wytr.item.armour.PineWynnterSweater.lore: The sweater has the quote "Let me NICK a few extra cookies for Craftmas" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.PinkWynnterSweater.lore: The sweater has the quote "Going HAM on Craftmas dinner tonight" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.Pisces.lore: The oddly uncomfortable helmet was hand sculpted from a mystic clay found only in the depths of Molten Heights. Not much is known about the substance.
wytr.item.armour.PostUltima.lore: These leggings are the last remaining piece of a historical set of armor, created with such power as to be thought impossible long ago.
wytr.item.armour.PropellerHat.lore: A tag on the inside of the hat reads: "Do not fly during thunderstorms! The wearer is liable for all injuries sustained while using this product."
wytr.item.armour.PurpleWynnterSweater.lo: The sweater has the quote "ICY you looking at my fancy duds" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.QuiltedCarapace.lore: This patchwork of shells from the Corkian Astrochelys makes for quite the statement sweater; it keeps your neck warm and besides, your foes' fashion fancies feel frivolous, anyway.
wytr.item.armour.Radiation.lore: Radioactive emissions caused by starfall seeps into the mind, the atoms, the Soul. Transfiguring organic matter into something new, something sinister. It's only through sheer force of will that victims of such a thing break free from themselves, and their imperfect vessels... into something beautiful.
wytr.item.armour.RagnisMail.lore: One of the few remaining standard issue mails that were used against the first hordes to emerge from the infamous portal over 1000 years ago.
wytr.item.armour.RedWynnterSweater.lore: The sweater has the quote "I'll never give you the COLD SHOULDER" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.Reliquiae.lore: Ancient and new hearts beat as one.
wytr.item.armour.Resolution.lore: In the moments before an all but inescapable death, time slows down, and the pace of battle becomes yours. By mastering the escape, you can face death on command, reaping the benefits at will before the reaper reaches you.
wytr.item.armour.Resurgence.lore: An antique passed from the Caritat wreckage into the hands of the outcast elves of Efilim. So to honor the memory of the selfless family as inspired their self-imposed exile, their strongest healing spells were imbued into it, and sent to those who needed them most.
wytr.item.armour.Revenant.lore: Those whose souls are lost to the Canyon of the Lost eternally seek form. They inhabit those who wear these boots, unknowingly dragging the soul of the wearer into their ranks if worn for too long, leaving a wandering husk.
wytr.item.armour.ReveredSilverMaskofLege: Revered Silver Mask of Legendary Victory

This ornate decorative mask, fashioned from pure silver, is awarded to those who have spent an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge and broken the mold by continuing to spend an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge.
wytr.item.armour.Ribcage.lore: "...as intimidating as the name sounds, you want your organs to be trapped in this kind of cage." -Excerpt from Human Anatomy For Fools, Cirh Nettan
wytr.item.armour.RuneboundChains.lore: You know better than anyone else that there’s always a sliver of truth behind the tallest of tales.
wytr.item.armour.Sagittarius.lore: The hide of the centaur is extraordinarily magical in the right hands. It is told to allow the user to gain the swiftness of the horse, but also leaves them vulnerable to hard hitting attacks.
wytr.item.armour.Sawdust.lore: Once cursed by a druid who had his grove chopped away by a greedy Villager, it was then purified and mass-produced for sale as armor, to the druid's utter disappointment.
wytr.item.armour.ScarletVeil.lore: You're seeing red... Time to see more of it.
wytr.item.armour.ScarletWynnterSweater.l: The sweater has the quote "Why be merry? CLAUS I said so" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.ScorchedAntiquity.lore: These hollowed spikes still hold the lingering embers of the event that formed this caldera long ago, lending an almost unnatural glow. It's a comforting warmth, though the force of the eruption remains dormant, primed for the slightest push.
wytr.item.armour.Scorpio.lore: The carapace of the common Maexi pet fire scarabs, while alone, only cause minor burns to the touch. However, when woven together, they produce a variety of cumulative effects.
wytr.item.armour.SevenLeagueBoots.lore: Bending the fabric of reality to allow the wearer to take massive strides, these boots are rumored to contain rogue djinni to power them.
wytr.item.armour.ShawlofGaea.lore: Despite being thin enough to blow away in the wind, this mineral-blended shawl holds the force of a supervolcano within its soft fabric.
wytr.item.armour.Shinespark.lore: There have been many attempts to create a reliable power system in Llevigar, and this plasma-charged helmet was reforged from a notable prototype.
wytr.item.armour.Slayer.lore: Many artifacts are found to incite rage in the wearer, and wizards old and new alike conjecture as to the purpose of them. Very few increase the latent abilities of the wearers to ensure havoc, and none to such a degree as these boots.
wytr.item.armour.SnowtreadBoots.lore: According to the tag on the heels, these boots leave a trail of snow no matter  where one walks with them.
wytr.item.armour.SodetaBoots.lore: These boots were standard issue to members of the prestigious, and now disbanded, Sodeta Guild, and given as a gift to the owners of Delnar Mansion one day.
wytr.item.armour.SoulInk.lore: Taken from the Archwraith by a pious Shaman, this chestplate was immediately abandoned. Its few users since have turned to an all-consuming desire to seek out and realign the last vestiges of purity remaining in the Kander Forest.
wytr.item.armour.Speaker: Speaker
wytr.item.armour.Spectre.lore: The dark spectres of the decayed forests have created an insidious helmet to drain the spirit of those who wear it, and become servants to their dark whims. Many have fallen to its allure.
wytr.item.armour.Spinneret.lore: "...Spiders have a weak point in the cephalothorax, essentially the neck. A small target, but it isn't as tough to chop through as the rest of them. ..." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3
wytr.item.armour.Springtrap.lore: "After nearly getting trapped in an iron maiden, I figure I can study  those mummies just as well from home." -Achper, Almuj Archaeologist
wytr.item.armour.Stalagmites.lore: Although these boots are crafted from corrupted stone, they do not exhibit any corruptive effects on their wearers. Speculation abounds as to the reason.
wytr.item.armour.Stardew.lore: Wybels have a strange attraction to cosmic magic, and many an owner will find them staring through the window at night. One, however, claims to have seen her Wybel making something out of white stardust. The abode was robbed shortly after, and the supposed item gone missing without confirmation of its existence.
wytr.item.armour.SteamjetWalkers.lore: A rogue inventor stole the plans for a steam jet booster from Corkus and reverse engineered them onto a set of boots. While effective, they are dangerous, prone to catastrophic failure.
wytr.item.armour.StiflingSpores.lore: The beauty of this peculiar grotto takes your breath away. Unfortunately, its spores do too...
wytr.item.armour.Stingy.lore: "You should see when the spiders fight over a meal. It looks ridiculous, legs flailing everywhere!" -Captain Enduyn, Ragni Legion 1st Division
wytr.item.armour.SweepingMajesty.lore: Echoes of the Fracturing persist in the Sky at scales unimaginable, implying a power so all-encompassing it leaves you in awe.
wytr.item.armour.Taciturn.lore: The Expanse holds an exigent paranoia, a hamartia for even the most renowned heroes. Only a survivor knows to hoard intelligence, showing their hand only when none will be left to recount it.
wytr.item.armour.Taurus.lore: The hide of the Touroto, an almost invincible Bull-like creature, is said to be pierced only by the horn of the Touroto itself, making it extremely valuable.
wytr.item.armour.TheBerserkersHelm.lore: Worn by a terrible berserker during his fanatical rampage through the land, his rage permeates this horned blackiron helmet.
wytr.item.armour.TheForgery.lore: While only a mockery of the original product, this line of helmets became wildly popular before legal disputes and safety concerns halted production.
wytr.item.armour.TheJinglingJester.lore: Jingle jangle, while shaking your bells. Jingle jangle come the pockets of cash... Catch the trickster, send them to hell," their money is gone and off you've dashed!
wytr.item.armour.TheSirensCall.lore: “I have hope in me the likes of which you could never imagine, and despair the likes of which you shall never fathom. If I cannot satisfy the one, then I will indulge the other.”
wytr.item.armour.TheSwarm.lore: The scratching in the walls is the only warning you get.
wytr.item.armour.ThirdEye.lore: The Bantisu monks have developed this enigmatic sigil in their years of meditation and study. It blesses the wearer with luck and powerful psionic ability.
wytr.item.armour.TimeRift.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] You only have limited time. But what if, you could experience that time again? And again, and again...
wytr.item.armour.TisaunsValor.lore: Tisaun, a warrior tasked to fend off a corrupted siege alone, could find only a thin shirt and rusted spear to use before the attack. He defeated all 1000 enemies without taking a scratch, and his bravery infused his gear with that same strength.
wytr.item.armour.TitaniumGrievers.lore: Crudely misshapen greaves made from haphazard scrap found about the Starfield. You sense a foreboding notion that donning such a thing would be the end of sensing anything at all.
wytr.item.armour.Titanomachia.lore: This is futile, a fight against odds so great you may as well challenge the force of fate itself. Yet there is pride to be found in delaying the inevitable, so stand your ground and fight to the end.
wytr.item.armour.TreasuredDiamondMaskofL: Treasured Diamond Mask of Legendary Victory

This excessively ornate to-the-point-of-being-wasteful decorative mask, laser-cut from a meter's worth of pure diamond, is given to those who have spent an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge, broken the mold by continuing to spend an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge, gone even further beyond spending unnecessary amounts of time completing the Legendary Challenge, and then pushed onward to prove that they will not stop spending unnecessary amounts of time completing the Legendary Challenge.
wytr.item.armour.TwilightGildedCloak.lor: An ephemeral moment in time captured by sheer force of magic, this ornately-crafted cloak is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.
wytr.item.armour.ValseVaincue.lore: The Wanderer; the Betrayer; the Lunatic.
wytr.item.armour.Vaward.lore: A once-great hero left behind these sturdy, reliable greaves, trusting those after her to be able to use their power to protect others, should they don them. Her courage fuels their wearers.
wytr.item.armour.VeneratedGoldMaskofLege: Venerated Gold Mask of Legendary Victory

This excessively ornate decorative mask, moulded from 24 carat gold, is awarded to those who have both spent an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge and broken the mold by continuing to spend an unnecessary amount of time completing the Legendary Challenge, and then gone even further beyond spending unnecessary amounts of time completing the Legendary Challenge.
wytr.item.armour.Venison.lore: This ancient Elven sacrificial mask contains only a sliver of its previous magic, yet the blessing of the Elven god Entia still greatly empowers those who don it.
wytr.item.armour.VentusTail.lore: Fashioned from the cut tails of the now extinct Venti, these nearly immaterial boots are light as air and crackle with lightning.
wytr.item.armour.Virgo.lore: These common leather boots were once owned by a barbarian with no magical prowess. Instead of enchanting it, he coated the soles in corrupted shards to punish those who opposed him.
wytr.item.armour.Wanderlust.lore: Are your heart, soul, and mind one? The ones who love are the most vulnerable. The ones who persist are the most detached. The ones who forget are the most naive. Only when you remove these impurities from your body could you reach the end.
wytr.item.armour.Warchief.lore: Sheer strength exudes from these Orcish relics, simple sandals ill-fitting to humans or Villagers. Enchanted with power and rage rather than magic, the strength that is provided when they are worn is unparalleled.
wytr.item.armour.WebPlate.lore: "I just need a little more spider silk to finish this vest!" -Lacrona, Detlas Tailor, found eaten by Nivla spiders
wytr.item.armour.WhiteWynnterSweater.lor: The sweater has the quote "SNOW way Craftmas can be bad in this sweater" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.armour.Windborne.lore: Orders, cannonfire, calls for surrender—the wind carries all. To ride the winds is to harness the lifeblood of battle, infiltrating up the veins of command with mere token resistance.
wytr.item.armour.WintersEssence.lore: These pure, snow-white leggings are rumored to have been crafted by the legendary ice mage Theorick. The people of Nesaak view them as cursed, seeking to destroy them in a bid to stop the endless winter surrounding them.
wytr.item.armour.YellowWynnterSweater.lo: The sweater has the quote "YELLOW- How's your Craftmas going" knitted onto the front.
wytr.item.weapon.Abolition.lore: "Those bloody zombies don't kip down at night, what makes you think a curfew might bally-well help?" -General Graken, Nemract Militia
wytr.item.weapon.Absolution.lore: A deep regret stains this weapon—once a healing implement of the scholar-priest, its gentle power was turned and twisted as his ideals and resolve were tested, and faltered. With its wielder long passed, perhaps it can finally be absolved of the atrocities committed by his hand... and remember the peace it has long forgotten.
wytr.item.weapon.Afterimage.lore: This wand is capable of attacks so fast that it appears to flicker in and out of existence. Anyone able to access its full potential will be seen as only a blur to their enemies.
wytr.item.weapon.Aftershock.lore: The Fracturing brought Ahms into a shattered sky, sundering cliffs into an archipelago against the void. The tremors that linger carry an ancient power, bringing mountains to heel with ease and leaving devastation in its wake.
wytr.item.weapon.Alizarin.lore: This bloody palette knife was used to kill only two people before it was abandoned - a killer who broke into a great artist's home, and the artist who struck the blow.
wytr.item.weapon.AlkaCometflinger.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and raw potential fuse to create an imposing presence, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for complete obliteration.
wytr.item.weapon.Alkatraz.lore: Soul-locking magic is one outlawed by Gavellian governments, only used by the most insidious and cruel of mages. One such enchantment looms dormant in this mundane-looking maul. Continued usage of the weapon threatens to release it upon the wielder, permanently binding them to the weapon.
wytr.item.weapon.AlmujsDaggers.lore: The reigning king of thieves in Almuj’s underworld would brandish this golden dagger to his enemies so fast, you wouldn’t even realise your wallet was now missing.
wytr.item.weapon.AncientWand.lore: It is thought that this primitive wand was used by early man to create the first spells. It is made from a wood that no longer exists.
wytr.item.weapon.Apocalypse.lore: To forge a weapon such as this from the cursed lava of the portal basin requires dozens, for each smith would lose themselves to the force of corruption before it is finished. The nightmarishly hooked blade serves no purpose but destruction, as intended.
wytr.item.weapon.Archangel.lore: The unwieldy, yet imposing stature of this massive sickle strikes awe into those who view it. Those who have the will to wield it, however, seem to garner respect from all those around them, as though they had become a god.
wytr.item.weapon.ArmaGauntlet.lore: Stories say that should anyone wield both of these fearsome gauntlets in battle, they will become unkillable in a fight. The second gauntlet, however, has never been found.
wytr.item.weapon.Az.lore: Mysterious runes, held by inexplicable ancient guardians, were once moulded together for study purposes. The experiment went awry, as the runic words Nii, Az, and Ek were combined in a reaction that resulted in the collapse of a civilization.
wytr.item.weapon.Bedruthan.lore: Stone shorn from mountains by the roiling sea gathered on the shores of Llevigar one day, washed onto the sand in the shape of a massive spear. It was taken as an omen, and the stones were forged into a true weapon.
wytr.item.weapon.Bismuthinite.lore: An extremely rare metallic ore only found within the island region of Corkus, it is normally used in decorative dyes. However, a mishap one day caused the discovery of strange and cumulative effects when exposed to traditional magicks.
wytr.item.weapon.Black.lore: Hewn from the great obsidian spires surrounding the massive Nether gate, this fiercely-hooked dagger absorbs light and magic energy alike to create a desolate void wherever it is wielded.
wytr.item.weapon.BladeofPurity.lore: The creator of this polished white blade insists that its true power will never be unlocked, for only those who are not influenced by the elements of the world know truly how to utilize it.
wytr.item.weapon.BladeofShade.lore: The fabled weapon of the titular dark Assassin, the blade's small stature hides its true powers. Shadows undulate about the hilt.
wytr.item.weapon.BlazingRuin.lore: One who forsook all others in pursuit of their own gain forced an extension of their own will into existence. This culmination of that will consumes all it touches.
wytr.item.weapon.Bloodbath.lore: Blood. Carnage. Death. Destruction. This is all Annihilation knows. A fury written into its very core, a violent rage building from an endless War. If it were to have its way, all of Wynn would fall to chaos.
wytr.item.weapon.Blossom.lore: A mystical sapling native to the shores of Mage Island has been fashioned into this simple staff. Even uprooted, you notice its continuous growth.
wytr.item.weapon.BlossomHaze.lore: And as the spring bursts, the blossom petals flutter in the wind amongst the ashes of your enemies.
wytr.item.weapon.Bluetooth.lore: Forged from the fang of a ferocious beast. Despite its small size, it can land blows at considerable range.
wytr.item.weapon.Bonder.lore: It looks like they spelled the name wrong...
wytr.item.weapon.BoughofFir.lore: Crafted from Mandragora roots and adorned with decorative wreaths of Elven pines, these wands are utilized in Efilim's solstice festivals to celebrate each passing year of Villager and Elven comradery.
wytr.item.weapon.Braker.lore: Seems like the name is misspelled a little bit.
wytr.item.weapon.BrassBrand.lore: Built by Cerid to accrue raw static charge from the surroundings and direct it at opponents, the blade's chief failing is that the wielder is not rendered immune to their own discharge as intended.
