wytr.item.weapon.Cascade.lore: A great magical cataclysm at Mage Island brought on by a strange, seemingly disconnected series of events resulted in this wand absorbing nearly uncontrollably high levels of magic.
wytr.item.weapon.Cataclysm.lore: Despite the existence of the Nether Portal, few believe that it is possible to open such rifts with sheer force alone. None believe that a tool with enough power to accomplish such a monumental feat could exist. And yet...
wytr.item.weapon.Cathedral.lore: "The gravestone for the brother of that man, Sayleros? For whatever reason, it didn't have a proper name on it." -Sacre, Saint's Row Priest
wytr.item.weapon.Chakram.lore: Despite appearing as a basic blade when held, strange spiritual magic changes its form into a sharp, ring-like cutting edge when used to attack. Only one person was known to master the weapon's abilities.
wytr.item.weapon.Chaleur.lore: This blackiron blade was left to sear in the desert for months on end by a fanatical berserker. It burned him alive as he cut down those who opposed him.
wytr.item.weapon.Chaser.lore: "My husband's such a scaredy-cat. What good is tomb raiding if you're not in the tomb?"  -Dr. Junes, Almuj Archaeologist
wytr.item.weapon.Clairvoyance.lore: The powerful psychic energies surrounding this bow are rumored to increase accuracy, though this has not been refuted by any reliable source.
wytr.item.weapon.ClashHook.lore: The wear on this humble war pick's blade has only made it more effective in combat, allowing its users to make unexpected parries of opponents' attacks by hooking and hitting through the weapon.
wytr.item.weapon.Clunderthap.lore: "It never rains here, but we hear the thunder echoing in the distance."  -Lanu, Almuj Archaeomancer
wytr.item.weapon.Cluster.lore: Perhaps one is weak. To be ignored. Perhaps two are not much better. But what of five? Ten? Twenty?...
wytr.item.weapon.Collapse.lore: Despite the light weight of the weapon, the spearhead has been made from incredibly dense cosmic stone. A strong enough impact can directly destroy matter. Due to this danger, it is sought after to be destroyed.
wytr.item.weapon.Continuum.lore: From nothing to everything, forever past to forever more, the vastness of eternity is obscured by the sameness of tomorrow.
wytr.item.weapon.Convergence.lore: As the void approaches nearer and nearer, the barrier between realms thins almost to a point... And yet, no matter how far you fall or how fast you fly, it will always lie just out of reach. Such is the indeterminate nature of the void, and its power that you harness.
wytr.item.weapon.Corpse.lore: "Catch a fresh-raised corrupted, it's like catching a soldier without his morning coffee. Stumbly and unfocused." -Enzan, Retired Ragni Soldier
wytr.item.weapon.Crackshot.lore: This heavy crossbow forces a strange compulsion in its users when wielded. They will often refuse to even shoot unless entirely certain of a hit.
wytr.item.weapon.Cryoseism.lore: One of the first dwarven theories of the increasing quakes in east Gavel was that the freezing of a Dogun town in the Heights also froze a massive underground spring, disrupting the earth and chain-reacting across the province.
wytr.item.weapon.Damnation.lore: "I got a name, known far and wide! Run along, you bandit scum, before you have to learn it the hard way!" -Sayleros' Brother, killed by bandits
wytr.item.weapon.Deadeye.lore: The weapon of the fearsome lone bandit, Rymek Luke, it is unique in that it is designed to fire small metal rounds instead of more traditional projectiles.
wytr.item.weapon.DeathsReach.lore: "We'll ensure that under our watch, all your families will be reunited!" -Haros, of the Banished Legion
wytr.item.weapon.DecayboundSpindle.lore: Decay spreads unseen, but you know it spreads, and that is enough.
wytr.item.weapon.Defibrillator.lore: "The first time I saw one of those zombies I nearly had a heart attack! The blighters are terrifying." -Rynend, Maltic Citizen
wytr.item.weapon.DetlasLegacy.lore: One of Detlas’ buildings was struck by lightning 60 years ago and burnt to the ground, apart from one wooden beam that began to glow. It was fashioned into an exclusive wand for resident mages.
wytr.item.weapon.Diablo.lore: One of the most unstable wands known to man, using the bark of the Flerisi trunk it reaps firey destruction upon its enemies.
wytr.item.weapon.Dislocater.lore: Often, the leader of brute gangs would use this dagger to threaten his followers into making sure they did not fail him.
wytr.item.weapon.Divergence.lore: Strangers held together by shared past, entwined in a fray, never to unite again.
wytr.item.weapon.Divzer.lore: Unruly magics of void and darkness are tamed within this bow's string. While those energies are never to be released, arrows fired from it fire at such blinding speeds so as to phase out of existence when they hit their target.
wytr.item.weapon.DuneKiln.lore: "You don't really advance much when it comes to ovens. For clay, glass, ceramics...it was perfected a long time ago." -Treous, Almuj Glassblower
wytr.item.weapon.EmpireBuilder.lore: This golden staff was recovered from deep within the tombs of Almuj. Nothing else was found in the room except the words 'Beware the user with unlimited imagination.'
wytr.item.weapon.Epoch.lore: This ornate bow holds a sinister beauty. Each rediscovery marks impending disaster, against any force that attempts to overcome it. Such is the inevitability of fate: irreverent to the will of masses, an epoch starts anew.
wytr.item.weapon.Eruption.lore: No one expected the WynnExcavation volcanic site to produce any valuable materials, but this heavy, obsidian-blend bow silenced the critics.
wytr.item.weapon.Ethereal.lore: Supposedly based off of the wand of master mage Ethe, this wand is plated with magic-focusing jewels and heavy gold, yet somehow remains entirely weightless.
wytr.item.weapon.Fangs.lore: "Not every spider is venomous, but do you really want to get bitten by them all to figure out which are?" -Alvin, Nivla Forest Resident
wytr.item.weapon.Fantasia.lore: The confusion of sentience creates unknown and marvelous threads and soundscapes. Joy, grief, hate, love, shock, calm, they reflect back into the pattern and song of the universe. The glow of the Weave, and this brilliant, breathtaking, pale imitation of it, too, resounds in the chorus of existence—one extra layer.
wytr.item.weapon.Fatal.lore: A mage by the name of Lero claims to have harnessed the sheer power of lightning using a magical staff, however, the weapon is very unreliable in a pinch.
wytr.item.weapon.FaustianContract.lore: Once a contract is formed, and before its details are discussed, a seal is placed on the human's body.
wytr.item.weapon.FierceThunder.lore: Every time this spear hits an enemy, a sharp electrical jolt hits the users hands that forces powerful lightning to release.
wytr.item.weapon.Fierte.lore: Only the most honourable warriors of Gavel's army are presented the fearsome, fiery spear forged from the rarest metals of the Molten Heights.
wytr.item.weapon.Fissure.lore: Dwarven folklore tells of this mighty maul, used by gods to break mountains, shape continents, and crack the earth to form caverns.
wytr.item.weapon.FlameshotHilt.lore: Found abandoned in the ruins of the Doguns, these odd weapons are designed to shoot jets of sheer flame instead of hitting enemies traditionally. They are in terrible disrepair, and none know how to fix them.
wytr.item.weapon.ForlornPursuit.lore: A hovercraft scrounged from voidstone. Stained glass dulled to bleak grays. Blueprints and notes in indecipherable tongues. Moments, lost in time—like so  much refuse from the world above.
wytr.item.weapon.Fractal.lore: Curious, isn't it, that unending complexity can feel so plain in one's hand, yet pull deeper than eyes can see and minds can fathom?
wytr.item.weapon.Freedom.lore: Freedom of soul, mind, and body are forced upon all those that this bow's arrows impact, and freedom of caring from the atrocities that such a dangerous weapon can inflict is given to all those that hold it.
wytr.item.weapon.Gaia.lore: The Dernel tribes revere various nature deities, each in their own unique fashions. One of the most notable was that of a lost tribe, who fashioned this blossoming stave as tribute to their deity of the earth itself.
wytr.item.weapon.GalesForce.lore: Those who have used this near-weightless bow all seem to tell tales of how they see Gale's spirit fighting alongside them.
wytr.item.weapon.GertSuperSpecialMagicUl: Well...it is a very pretty-looking stick, but aside from that it just appears to be a plain old stick.
wytr.item.weapon.GlacialCrest.lore: Used for endurance training on the Icy Islands, this bow forces the wielder's body temperature to drop to near-hypothermic levels.
wytr.item.weapon.Glare.lore: The blazing sun has been revered by many druidic sects as a god in its own right, and the jewel in this brilliant wand glows with the brightness of their holy star.
wytr.item.weapon.GrandDesign.lore: It’s a gravity as abstract as it is physical, of phenomena so fascinating one can’t help but be pulled in.
wytr.item.weapon.Grandmother.lore: The very first crossbow in existence was claimed to be utterly indestructible, but it is only true to a fault. The item cannot be broken, but solely because all damage to it is instead reflected onto the user. As its age is uncountably ancient, wielders will find themselves rapidly aging and withering away with even a mere touch.
wytr.item.weapon.Grimtrap.lore: Found at the site of the Caritat Mansion, this simple-looking glove is bathed in dark presence. It wracks those who wear it with pain, and instills the belief that the only way to end the pain is not to remove the item, but to inflict that same torment upon all others.
wytr.item.weapon.Guardian.lore: A vow of protection hangs over this spear, now inhabited by the spirit of a legendary heroine. Even simply a glimpse of the burning blade will instill a feeling of protection and security, and that feeling will hold true if one is brave enough to wield it.
wytr.item.weapon.Hadal.lore: Carved from unknown parts of a sea creature unseen, the goliath scales of this effigy of the deep bring forth...a pull. A weight, a pressure. A terrible, crushing depth brought onto the holder, blanketing them like nostalgia. Their owner watches, part of itself acutely aware of its missing pieces.
wytr.item.weapon.Hanafubuki.lore: The most dangerous enemy is one you cannot see. Hidden amidst a flurry of petals comes an avalanche of blows, in one moment dissolving mountains and forests into a growing amalgam, leaving a wake of vibrant bloom in the next.
wytr.item.weapon.HarosOar.lore: The weathered oar of Haros, the outcast ferryman of Charon's Forsaken Legion. Magical implements have been jury-rigged onto the silver pole, glowing dull out of his bony grasp.
wytr.item.weapon.HarshNoise.lore: Corkian technology was not the first to create an item that is capable  of recording noise. Artifacts from Time Valley were found to record ambient  sounds and distort them into ear-splitting sonic bursts.
wytr.item.weapon.Harwrol.lore: The runes carved onto the spear shift appearance so quickly as to be illegible, but those who wield it supposedly will learn their meaning.
wytr.item.weapon.HashrClaw.lore: "Betrayal stings sharper than a scorpion's tail, and festers worse than the poison inside."   -Attributed to Hashr
wytr.item.weapon.HeatDeath.lore: Everything slowly loses heat, and will eventually stop moving. Are you prepared?
wytr.item.weapon.Hellstrand.lore: The Order of the Abyss crafted this bow in opposition to the House of Talor's holy relic. Holding it for too long will strain and warp the user's mind.
wytr.item.weapon.HelmSplitter.lore: One of Skien's many deadly weapons. This warhammer, despite the massive weight of the hammerhead, was able to be swung by Skien fast enough to be a blur.
wytr.item.weapon.Heracul.lore: Reconstructed from mere wooden scraps of its former self, this extremely heavy crossbow still contains immense power. It was intended for use with a lost suit of armor, of which only one piece remains.
wytr.item.weapon.Hero.lore: Enigmatically, this weapon will only show itself to those who believe themselves to be worth nothing, or to be weak. While utilizing this weapon will greatly strengthen one's resolve, it will disappear when it is no longer needed, going to the next wielder.
wytr.item.weapon.Hesperium.lore: Watch as they receive your gift of imminent disaster and endless fallout.
wytr.item.weapon.Hourglass.lore: "I saw that spider queen once. It felt like it was only a matter of time before she found my home, so I moved here." -Babhla, Nivla Bowl Merchant
wytr.item.weapon.HymnoftheDead.lore: "The dead can still hear. I figure a lullaby might help convince them to sleep a bit longer." -Merloni, Saint's Row Priest
wytr.item.weapon.Idol.lore: Intricate carvings and images, almost like that of a totem pole, cover the shaft of this marvelous trident, dredged up from the Seavale Reef. Foreign magics heighten the senses of its user in battle, but also instills a longing for the ocean. Many have succumbed to this urge and drowned themselves.
wytr.item.weapon.Ignis.lore: This bow, used by the dwarves to land the final blow in the slaughter of Garaheth, is extremely powerful. Special fire resistant gloves must be worn at all times to prevent burns to the user.
wytr.item.weapon.Ignition.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] Forged with flaming scales shorn from Ozoth, the fabled Golden Ninja of the Canyon of the Lost hunted his prey relentlessly using this lightweight, yet harder than steel, polearm.
wytr.item.weapon.Iklaj.lore: "I am not making this up! That spider teleported ONTO MY FACE!" -Stiba, Elemental Researcher
wytr.item.weapon.Immolation.lore: The act of self-immolation is never taken lightly, and is always a sacrifice. This idol was carved to honor one such instance, in which a master of flame burned through his life force in a final act of heroism—purging an encroaching army of the undead, saving the people of the jungle from destruction.
wytr.item.weapon.Impulse.lore: Prolonged exposure to the corruption may cause sudden bursts of madness in soldiers. To assure themselves of their sanity, some have even begun to play tricks on their brethren.
wytr.item.weapon.Inferno.lore: The Dogun God Garaheth was actually an immense fire demon occupying the bowels of Molten Heights. Although unwise, the Dwarves forged a demonic dagger using his tooth in celebration of his slaughter.
wytr.item.weapon.Infinitesimal.lore: For when one needs to carve the smallest stone or pick the smallest lock, the subtleties of precision approach impossibility.
wytr.item.weapon.Infinity.lore: If you reach for ammunition from your quiver, as long as you have a single arrow, you will find you never run out.
wytr.item.weapon.Influence.lore: This knife does not belong in your hands... yet somehow it feels right at home.
wytr.item.weapon.InfusedHiveBow.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this bow has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its string radiates a spectrum of colors.
wytr.item.weapon.InfusedHiveDagger.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this dagger has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It leaves afterimages that pulsate in a spectrum of colors.
wytr.item.weapon.InfusedHiveRelik.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this relik has been infused with energy from all five known elements. The head gleams in a spectrum of colors.
wytr.item.weapon.InfusedHiveSpear.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this spear has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its tip shimmers in a spectrum of colors.
wytr.item.weapon.InfusedHiveWand.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this wand has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It subtly glows in a spectrum of colors.
wytr.item.weapon.IronKnuckle.lore: These bulky-looking gauntlets are actually extremely lightweight, being created of a magical elf-blessed iron alloy blend.
wytr.item.weapon.IronString.lore: Many said making a bow out of iron would be slow and wasteful, but the weight of the iron arrow can pierce even stone.
wytr.item.weapon.Ivory.lore: The holy blade of the House of Talor was crafted of pure unicorn horns, and consecrated by a hundred priests. Evil spirits are driven away by its mere presence.
wytr.item.weapon.IvyWhip.lore: "The vines you'll find among the foilage make for great rope!" -Alekin's Guide to Plant Fiber Cordage
wytr.item.weapon.JawBreaker.lore: "Bandit attacks losing you sleep? Free fighting classes here! Only 10  emeralds- they won't know what hit 'em!" -Almuj Self-Defense Class Advertisement
wytr.item.weapon.KahontsiOhstyen.lore: Wielded by the chief of the Tromsian jungle's zombie tribes, the augmentable crystals within it focus natural elemental energies to intense levels.
wytr.item.weapon.Karma.lore: "When payback is the rule of the land, it feels safest to do nothing."  -Ormrod, Self-exiled Almuj Resident
wytr.item.weapon.Labyrinth.lore: Left. Right. Left. Right. They are desperate for an escape, merely playthings in a maze of your design. Left. Left. Right.  Turn back. When mountains of stone can shift at your command, their world is reduced to a single path. Left. Right. Does it ever end?
wytr.item.weapon.Lament.lore: When the lost city of Sarnfic sunk beneath the depths, nothing but the bubbles of screams and this single wand surfaced. When used, you can still hear the towns lament.
wytr.item.weapon.LegendarySmasher.lore: Many have tried to duplicate the properties of this spear, but very few have succeeded in enchanting a spearhead with explosive magic that does not cause the spear itself to explode.
wytr.item.weapon.Locrian.lore: Skien's trust in others was shattered permanently by the wielder of this dagger, who fell to the corruption and attacked his legion during a great corrupted siege.
wytr.item.weapon.Lower.lore: The name has got to be misspelled... It doesn't even make any sense!
wytr.item.weapon.LunarSpine.lore: From the Nether Gate, a shard of cosmic stone was ejected. Its purity was defiled, and the first man to wield it went mad, raving about the fall of the cosmos' beauty.
wytr.item.weapon.Macabre.lore: "Only the most wicked in Gavel could dream of a circumstance as what plagues this Wynn province." -King of Ragni
wytr.item.weapon.Maelstrom.lore: Lost by master sailor Carvel in a massive storm, it was carried all the way out to the city of Selchar, where it was found spewing seafoam and lightning bolts.
wytr.item.weapon.MalevolentUrge.lore: You wouldn't even think of committing these atrocities, would you? But what if you weren't the one in control?
wytr.item.weapon.MalticsOldSpear.lore: This short spear was the first weapon to be produced by the villagers for sale. They are old, but strong.
wytr.item.weapon.Match.lore: "Controlled burns are healthy, but it's clear why no one wants to do them." -Darek, Alekin Trailblazer
wytr.item.weapon.Maul.lore: "If you squish a spider egg, sometimes little spiders pop out. So, squish the whole area instead!" -Captain Fenor, Detlas Legion
wytr.item.weapon.Mephistophelian.lore: When the two opposing Realms come to blows, War lashes out with blind enmity. Such is the nature of a Devil, each born from the hate those two Beasts bear.
wytr.item.weapon.MesarockArch.lore: The two mesa tribes once were allies until their sacred totems were stolen. Before that time, however, they often shared their talents, and this bow hewn from mesa stone was one such lost craft.
wytr.item.weapon.Miasma.lore: "I have to wonder just how healthy slime found in the depths of a desert  cavern can be to drink." -Eluzterp, Almuj resident
wytr.item.weapon.Monster.lore: This wand merges with the user on touch, bringing about horrific changes to them. Elongated nails, sharp teeth and the ability to breathe fire are trademarks of the beast.
wytr.item.weapon.Morrowind.lore: One of many lost artifacts from the legendary Wind Fortress, the engraving appears to be a cryptic clue to where the Fortress fell. "We shall be found among the dark winds of the morrow."
wytr.item.weapon.Narcissist.lore: The world revolves around you, after all. It's high time you spread the news!
wytr.item.weapon.NemractsRage.lore: A year-long monsoon soaked this Nemract-made bow so much, that it has harnessed the very essence of water.
wytr.item.weapon.NeptaFloodbringer.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and immense wisdom meld to create a commanding aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for dominion over all.
wytr.item.weapon.Nirvana.lore: Spiritual enlightenment is a goal that many monks hope to one day grasp the barest glimpse of, often thought to be a goal that must be worked towards over a lifetime. Holding this polished, translucent blade will instantly induce that lofty state until it is let go.
wytr.item.weapon.Nullification.lore: The diminutive stature of this item belies its abilities. Absorbing and expelling magical energy in precise bursts, it protects the user from all manner of attacks while punishing those who dare strike.
wytr.item.weapon.Oblivion.lore: This sacrificial kris, fallen from the peak of the Tower of Ascension, is completely hollow. To wield it is to invite to yourself the same hollowness. To become such an aberration, to unwrite yourself in pursuit of power...it must be fed of its wielder til only the barest existence remains.
wytr.item.weapon.OhmsWish.lore: "If anyone finds this, leave it at my Gale's gravesite. I promised her a memento, too." This inscription is extremely weathered.
wytr.item.weapon.OluxsPrizedBow.lore: This expertly crafted bow was whittled by a cryptid-researching fanatic. Its frame was cut from the very toughest tree roots.
wytr.item.weapon.OluxsPrizedDagger.lore: This expertly crafted dagger was smithed by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It can chop through even the thickest of the swamp's clay with ease.
wytr.item.weapon.OluxsPrizedRelik.lore: This expertly crafted relik was notched by a cryptid-researching fanatic. Its feathers and baubles chime with a soothing melody.
wytr.item.weapon.OluxsPrizedSpear.lore: This expertly crafted spear was forged by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shines brilliantly in even the weakest sunlight.
wytr.item.weapon.OluxsPrizedWand.lore: This expertly crafted wand was shaped by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shimmers with the purest water from the swamp.
wytr.item.weapon.Olympic.lore: When one has climbed the highest mountain, traversed the vastest plain, what is left to conquer? One challenges the human limit, and attempts to push beyond what any has accomplished before. Sculpted in honor of the first champion, this idol emboldens you to best your greatest opponent: yourself.
wytr.item.weapon.Overdrive.lore: Holding this relik sends sparks through your veins, making your heart beat fast. And faster. And faster and faster and--
wytr.item.weapon.PanicZealot.lore: They must know what you went through. They must suffer the same as you did.
wytr.item.weapon.PhoenixWing.lore: The magically rejuvenating properties of phoenix ash were imbued into this grand stave in its creator's bid to gain immortality.
wytr.item.weapon.PlagueStaff.lore: Carried by the Olux Plague Doctor, this simple-looking stick subtly oozes with an unidentifiable substance that is invigorating to the holder, and lethally venomous to anything else.
wytr.item.weapon.Proxima.lore: This spear is bright enough that it can cause blindness if you look directly at it. Its immense power is limited by its weight; the weapon is nearly impossible to lift.
wytr.item.weapon.Prymari.lore: This staff was expertly crafted from fragile spun glass, and tinted with various magical foci that bend light into its most raw components.
wytr.item.weapon.Pulsar.lore: The density of this weapon is almost immeasurable. Despite being light and easy to wield, the spear seems to have its own gravitational pull, slowly dragging enemies closer and making it nearly impossible to put down.
wytr.item.weapon.Pure.lore: Carved directly from the mysterious rock that hit Gavel 50 years ago, this pure white wand glows with cosmic energy unknown.
wytr.item.weapon.Putrid.lore: "Leave us down here to die, why don't you all. Just turn us into another statistic and be done, huh?" -Ragamal, Nemract Sewer Dweller
wytr.item.weapon.Pyrexia.lore: "I always thought Yahya was venom-addled, but the symptoms don't match..." -Pyeka, Alekin Herbalist
wytr.item.weapon.Quetzalcoatl.lore: The great serpent of Ahms was said to be a bringer of wisdom in days long past, revered by the inhabitants of the region. Totems like this one were crafted as an act of worship, though as belief faded over time, so too were these idols lost and destroyed. Only one remains.
wytr.item.weapon.ReaperofSoul.lore: A grave digger uncovered this blade from the resting place of a notorious pirate that pillaged the islands of the ocean for four decades.
wytr.item.weapon.Recursion.lore: To call an end a new beginning implies there ever was a beginning, or ever will be an end.
wytr.item.weapon.RedCandle.lore: The flickering flame atop this simple wand is a marvel of magic. It always burns at a comfortable heat, cannot scorch skin even if touched, and never can be snuffed out under any circumstance.
wytr.item.weapon.Relic.lore: Despite being proven unrelated, this enigmatic bow was the lynchpin to beginning the great search for the Relics.
wytr.item.weapon.RemikasRighteousness.lo: Despite this mace never seeing use by Remikas, it was seen as a symbol of the might of his rule over Gavel. Its true abilities in battle have never been seen.
wytr.item.weapon.Resonance.lore: The power to join oneself with the lifeblood of the earth has long eluded sects of fanatical druids and shamans. One such cult found a way, and subsequently wiped itself out in the process, their flesh turning to stone and veins forming new rivers.
wytr.item.weapon.Reticence.lore: Many old mages had to perform lengthy incantations to make potent even their simplest spells. A mage cursed to be mute, however, brought upon a revolution to spellcasting through this simple wand.
wytr.item.weapon.ReturntoEther.lore: This enigmatic weapon can suddenly blink out of reality with no warning only to appear exactly where it was left later. Artificers have determined that almost the entire bow, by all known laws of nature and magic, should not exist.
wytr.item.weapon.Rewind.lore: Time moves in strange ways around this translucent blade, speeding and slowing, starting and stopping, with no observable reasoning or pattern.
wytr.item.weapon.Rikter.lore: 릭터는 지진을 뜻하는 고대 윈어로, 이 거대한 전투 망치에 맞은 적들의 뼈가 갈라지고 으스러지는 모습에 이러한 이름이 붙었습니다
wytr.item.weapon.RoilingRuckus.lore: Not knowing what's going on is the best part!
wytr.item.weapon.Sage.lore: Discipline and experience is channeled into these wands for 10 years in the Bantisu monastery of the canyon, in the hope that they will pass on its teachings to less experienced users.
wytr.item.weapon.Sanies.lore: "Can anyone else understand that General Graken? Because I can't." -Commander Takan, Nemract Militia
wytr.item.weapon.Scorpion.lore: This dagger has no blade. Instead, it is layered with the stingers of the Black Shadow Scorpion, which has the ability to vanish entirely from its prey.
wytr.item.weapon.Scythe.lore: A psychopath claiming herself to be Death incarnate used this dark-bladed scythe on a killing spree that lasted over a year. It reaped hundreds of lives, including her own.
wytr.item.weapon.SerpentsKiss.lore: "I bet those sewer-dwellers have horrible morning breath." -Folzoy, Maltic Escort
wytr.item.weapon.SilkSlasher.lore: "Cut a web, and its owner will feel it and come out. That's your chance to strike." -Lieutenant Van, Detlas 2nd Regiment
wytr.item.weapon.Singularity.lore: The existence of all things is reflected in the otherworldly jewels of this grand staff, dense enough to have its own gravitational pull. Users have reported their limbs being stretched after usage.
wytr.item.weapon.Sitis.lore: Wielding it for too long will leave one a dessicated husk, as this dull blade slowly absorbs all liquids around it.
wytr.item.weapon.Sketiq.lore: "As much as they're terrifying, at least those lousy skeletons give us lots of bonemeal for the crops!" -Bylvis, Katoa Ranch Farmer
wytr.item.weapon.SkinPiercer.lore: The average bow can boast a range of skills, but unlike this one, not every bow can penetrate through any organic skin, including dragon hide.
wytr.item.weapon.SkullBreaker.lore: "Even a corrupted would get crushed by one of these!" -Roche 'Stone-thrower' Diamant, Ragni Citizen
wytr.item.weapon.Slider.lore: The spelling seems to have been botched.
wytr.item.weapon.Sol.lore: "The sun and related symbols appear quite often in these ancient glyphs.  Interesting, but unsurprising, no?" -Svin, Legend Keeper
wytr.item.weapon.SongofSolitude.lore: It is an apathy born from lonely desperation with which one sends a blinding ray as their signal flare, uncaring if it hails friend or foe.
wytr.item.weapon.Soundwave.lore: This bow's thick string fails to shoot arrows effectively, but instead produces low frequency sound waves that erupt from the source in all directions. The sound can implode the eardrums of an enemy with a single strum.
wytr.item.weapon.Spiritshock.lore: Recovered from the Lexdale Penitentiary, this grisly bow holds destructive capabilities. Used to carry out executions, a precise enough shot can shatter the soul of those it hits.
wytr.item.weapon.Spring.lore: Arrows fired by this bow are pure ice, but when they hit the enemy, burst into magical water, flash-freezing all that it touches. The frost burns will never heal.
wytr.item.weapon.Sprout.lore: "The plants loathe to take hold upon the red stone. And so, we must hunt instead."  -Caras, Owl Tribesman
wytr.item.weapon.Stabsand.lore: The art of endurance fighting is a skill lost to time. However, a thief that to this day has not been caught, imbued this dagger with the very same ability.
wytr.item.weapon.Stale.lore: "There's never new water flowing into those sewers. It all cycles back into itself...not natural." -Jenprest, Ragni Legion 2nd Division
wytr.item.weapon.StaveoftheLegends.lore: Crafted exclusively by the Temple of the Legends' mages, this stave is honorary to Mages who best the Temple's Grand Magus.
wytr.item.weapon.Sting.lore: "I swear on my life those spiders were covered in spikes! Go out there, see if I'm wrong!" -Suri, Elemental Researcher
wytr.item.weapon.Stinger.lore: If it weren't for that stray mark, this would be spelled correctly...
wytr.item.weapon.Stratiformis.lore: The Elves managed to harness the power of air itself, forming a bow made entirely of air currents, allowing the user to move swift like the wind, but vulnerable to attacks.
wytr.item.weapon.StyxsGrab.lore: "Never wish to see a dead loved one again. In this day and age, they'll come back to see you." -Mylo, Nemract Conscript
wytr.item.weapon.Sunstar.lore: Once known as the Doomsday Weapon, it was ultimately never used for its intended purpose - its solar focus was cracked upon the day of its completion. All but a fraction of its energy was expelled, obliterating its creators, but overwhelming magical force still pulses and thrums through the web of fractures in its design.
wytr.item.weapon.SuspendedSoliloquy.lore: No one can hold you down anymore.
wytr.item.weapon.Syncope.lore: The soul of a Devil is so hot with hatred that their  bodies melt like candle wax, coming off in molten globs of flesh until only black bones remain.
wytr.item.weapon.Tachypsychia.lore: You will probably irreversibly harm yourself with this, but when has that ever stopped you?
wytr.item.weapon.TemporalLantern.lore: No eyes see past the dark fog that enshrouds the future. But if you could perhaps light the way, what would you see? Invigorating hope? Or a warning to be heeded?
wytr.item.weapon.TenFootPole.lore: I'm not touching this with a... well. Yeah.
wytr.item.weapon.TheBerserk.lore: Forged from unbreakable obsidian eras ago, this heavy hammer has crushed many foes with a single swing.
wytr.item.weapon.TheDivide.lore: Once having held unstoppable amounts of magic, being forced to fuse into one form locked away all but the smallest sliver of their power.
wytr.item.weapon.TheExile.lore: This indestructible dagger was found floating in the magma of the Molten Heights, with a lament from its exiled smith carved onto the hilt.
wytr.item.weapon.TheSwordfish.lore: The ocean's bounty is full of many strange things. Sailor's tales of a peculiar fish with a snout like a sword and the unbelievable stories of its power thus inspired fanciful ideas in blacksmiths. The results speak for themselves.
wytr.item.weapon.Thriller.lore: "And no one's going to save us from the beasts about to strike. We've seen horrors stare us in the eyes, and we're fighting for our lives." -Poe, Nemract Sewer Dweller
wytr.item.weapon.ThrundaRipsaw.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and consuming fury combine to create a deadly aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for utter cataclysm.
wytr.item.weapon.Thrundacrack.lore: The raw aspect of thunder, though claimed to be harnessed by a mage in a wand, has only been truly tamed by this mighty blade. Combined electric and life-draining magic intertwine and bring forth the truest, most frightening power of all Thunder.
wytr.item.weapon.Thunderbolt.lore: This bow has no string. Instead, a thin lightning-like thread is strung upon it. It is said to be limited only by the speed of the user.
wytr.item.weapon.Tidebinder.lore: This mysterious, half-liquid trident apparently holds the secret magics to control the ocean's ebb and flow. It is incapable of touching solid ground.
wytr.item.weapon.TisaunsProof.lore: The wear upon this broken old battle spear does not affect its ability in battle. The souls of a thousand fallen warriors resound within it.
wytr.item.weapon.Toaster.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] This peculiar weapon was once wielded by the firey warrior Igbar, who used it to great effect in endurance competitions.
wytr.item.weapon.TorrentialTide.lore: The tides of the ocean, once bound, became useful magic power sources. They were once utilized for weapons, but to harness the unstable force of the raging sea was considered too dangerous.
wytr.item.weapon.Toxoplasmosis.lore: Can you feel the burning inside? Something has made itself at home. Time to tuck away the parts of you it has no need for, to shuffle your little brain around so you may Carry. Carry and Spread. Give it a new home—melting you down is how it says thank you. Be grateful, won't you?
wytr.item.weapon.Trance.lore: Down. Your enemies will fall slack. Deeper. Do you know this compulsion you bring? Deeper still. This implement, reaching from within and without. Even deeper. Souls and wills to command at the flex of a finger. Almost gone. It is my compulsion, too great to ignore. It is my implement, too strong to resist. My puppets, too deep to escape. Drop.
wytr.item.weapon.Tremolo.lore: "It feels like all these "ancient" civilizations have better tech than we do nowadays."  -Knox, Corkus Immigrant and Sandstorm Vandals bandit
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedArchpriest.lore: It seems stronger at first glance, but upon closer inspection the blade is rather...soft?
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedCursedBow.lore: "100% curse-free or your money back!" The merchant explained that this policy is not legally binding after you read it.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedDarkNeedle.lore: The magic in this wand seems much weaker than normal...and there's a rather rude message written on the handle.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedEcholocation.lo: Did the merchant really think that adding severed bat wings to the weapon would make it more authentic?
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedFlareBlitz.lore: The weapon nearly catches fire during the merchant's demonstration. He still refuses to discount it despite this.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedHellRaiser.lore: The blade is covered in tape that's been scribbled on in order to make it look fiery. This doesn't seem like a wise purchase.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedLongBow.lore: Apparently, they thought to make a long bow better, they should make it longer. You can barely hold it.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedLullaby.lore: The inscribed lyrics have been scratched out and replaced with a barely-legible insult.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedMelange.lore: There are parts from at least six separately recognizable weapons mashed together to make this. There's no way it's effective.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedPhoenix.lore: According to the merchant, the wand is extra flammable, so that it can burn up and disappear with all the mages quicker.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedRadiance.lore: The craftsmanship on this bow is rather poor. The paint on the "crystals" is chipping...
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedScalpel.lore: The blade actually looks to be of good quality, unlike the other products. The only problem is the questionable stain covering most of it.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedSteelBuster.lor: It is significantly heavier than usual...you can't tell if that is good or not, in this case.
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedVartija.lore: The guard on the spear is smaller, but at least twice as thick. What purpose does that have?
wytr.item.weapon.UpgradedWhisper.lore: The blade seems sharper than normal, but it also seems rather brittle. The smithing was obviously a hack-job...
wytr.item.weapon.WanderersPurpose.lore: To look and say “I will go there,” and to keep going until you find it... that’s what’s important.
wytr.item.weapon.Warden.lore: "I've been wishin' I was dead for a long time."
wytr.item.weapon.Warp.lore: The notorious and erratic magical inventor Gawrick once attempted to make teleportation scrolls obsolete, by creating items which would allow the user to phase into an ethereal state to move unhindered. He did not account for the physical ramifications of this process, however.
wytr.item.weapon.WavesRaiser.lore: The mystery of the ocean’s appearance has eluded scholars for centuries. It is believed that many years ago, warlocks used wands like this one in an attempt to submerge the world.
wytr.item.weapon.Weathered.lore: A relic of the past in Time Valley was weathered down to a dagger by the sheer power of the wind. When used in battle, mysterious intertwined wind and time magic give it no physical presence.
wytr.item.weapon.WebSpitter.lore: "And you thought walking into a cobweb was bad." -Ope, Ragni Botanist
wytr.item.weapon.WitherheadsElbow.lore: Wielded by the master of the Decrepit Sewers Dungeon, the arrows of this bow causes the target's body to slowly wither away.
wytr.item.weapon.WybelPaw.lore: Even reduced to just the bones, you can't help but feel bad for the poor thing this paw came from.
wytr.item.weapon.ZephraShredder.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and sheer rage intertwine to create a fearsome sight, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for total destruction.
wytr.item.weapon.Zero.lore: The unstable power within this bow is capable of great destruction, but seems to zero out at the most crucial moments in battle. Only the most skillful archers can wield this weapon with confidence.
